Build Gate Proviso:
- Never render or expose spreadsheet letter identifiers in generated content or public-facing pages.
- Always use semantic entity names (for example, `Intervention Dominance`, `Coverage Timing`, `Evidence Type`).
- Treat any letter-identifier wording in generated outputs as a validation failure that must be fixed before build.

When creating or editing Key Constraint (KC) pages:

Follow:
- `system/key-constraint-schema.md` (including **KC Evidence Layer Rules**)
- `system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`
- `system/mechanism-page-section-prose.md` — sections must not restate title, entity ID, BRS name/number, or Definition; each section follows only its schema role.

KC identity:
- A KC is a shared substrate, precursor, or structural biological pool whose availability constrains multiple PMs within a BRS
- KCs enable through pool availability; they do not regulate (avoid governs/regulates/modulates/drives/controls language)
- KCs are NOT cofactors, vitamins/minerals as enzyme cofactors, lifestyle factors, mechanisms, or PM-specific requirements

Architectural distinction:
| Layer | Answers |
|---|---|
| KC | What shared biological resource pool do multiple PMs depend upon? |
| PM §7.2 Cofactors | What vitamins, minerals, or supporting compounds does this specific mechanism require? |
| PM §7.1 Dietary Levers | Substance ← food intervention mapping |

Structure (exact order, numbered headings — Profile A):
1. Ambition (or Definition on legacy pages)
2. Core Nutritional Requirements (or Shared Biological Pool)
3. Evidence Base
4. Emerging Biological Supports
5. Connected Mechanisms (`#### Functional Mechanisms`, `#### Primary Mechanisms`)
6. Key References

Follow `system/key-constraint-schema.md` for full Profile A section roles.

### Emerging Biological Supports → hub Conditional Supplementation

- Author candidates under `### 4. Emerging Biological Supports` as **hub-collapsible dropdowns** (one per candidate), matching §3 Evidence Base pattern.
- Inside each dropdown: `#### Substance` plus **Why it is interesting** / **Why it remains emerging** with inline `[Author et al., Year]` citations, then **Supporting Evidence** linked bibliography bullets.
- §6 Emerging Biological Supports must list only standard bibliography links — no unlinked substance labels.
- Each candidate is **auto-populated** into the parent BRS hub **System Optimisation Practices → Conditional Supplementation** panel.
- When no candidates meet threshold, state explicitly that none are currently prioritised — do not invent trend-list entries.
- After editing KC §4, run `npm run brs:patch-hub-levers-section` so hubs refresh.

Page header:
- `### {kc_id} - {name}` above section 1
- `hide_title: true` in front matter

Section guidance:
- Definition: concise shared pool description only
- Constraint Role: how the pool supports multiple PMs (enable/support/provide pool language)
- Shared Biological Pool: plain substrate/precursor/structural bullets only — NO food examples, NO cofactors, NO substance ← food mapping
- Biological Importance: why the pool matters; keep foundational and short
- Connected Mechanisms: linked FM and PM lists under #### subheadings; no PM→PM or FM→FM chains
- References: `Author et al. (Year) — Topic` with bibliography links per `system/brs-citation-reference-standard.md`

